name: SKAdTestError.Code
desc: Enumerated error codes related to ad network testing in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureInvalidKey
items.desc: The public key isn’t a valid cryptographic key, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureInvalidOrder
items.desc: The order of the parameters in the signature is invalid, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingAdNetworkId
items.desc: The signature is missing an ad network identifier, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingAppAdamId
items.desc: The signature is missing the app item identifier for the advertised app, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingCampaignId
items.desc: The signature is missing the campaign identifier, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingFidelityType
items.desc: The signature is missing the fidelity type, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingNonce
items.desc: The signature is missing the nonce, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingSourceAppAdamId
items.desc: The signature is missing the source app item identifier, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureMissingTimestamp
items.desc: The signature is missing a timestamp, in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureUnknownError
items.desc: An unknown error occurred with the signature in the testing environment.

items.name: case signatureVerificationFailed
items.desc: The signature verification failed in the testing environment.

items.name: case excessivePostbacks
items.desc: Too many postbacks submitted to the test session.

items.name: case invalidConversionValue
items.desc: The conversion value isn’t valid, in the testing environment.

items.name: case invalidRunnerUpPostback
items.desc: A non-winning postback is defined with a version prior to version 3, in the testing environment.

items.name: case malformedPostbacks
items.desc: The postback in the testing environment is malformed.

items.name: case missingPostbacks
items.desc: The testing environment doesn’t have any postbacks.

items.name: case misplacedWinnerPostback
items.desc: A winning postback wasn’t found in the first position, in the testing environment.

items.name: case missingWinningPostback
items.desc: The testing environment is missing a winning postback.
